    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-05T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-05T20:00:00-05:00" n="251"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">703.94/4030: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-06T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 6, 1932—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me last night that having heard of the
                    despatch from Japan of a division of Japanese troops to Shanghai the Chinese had
                    no other recourse but to send reenforcements to their hard-pressed forces at
                    Shanghai. He wished us to understand that this was not meant to be in violation
                    of their acceptance of the proposals of the note in reference to cessation of
                    troop movements but merely to meet a new phase already instituted by the <pb
                        facs="0334" n="230" xml:id="pg_230"/> Japanese. He expressed urgently the
                    hope that we would not permit Japanese to use Settlement as a screen for landing
                    of reenforcements. He is very much worried about situation. He said Chinese
                    aeroplanes had been instructed to keep away from Settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
